Process Hazard Review - The original process hazard analysis (PHA) consistent with the requirements of RMProgram and Process Safety Management (PSM) was conducted at the Hattiesburg facility in July 2012 utilizing a Hazards and Operability (HAZOP) approach   Air Products conducted the original PHA on the Hydrogen tank (which is their scope of supply) and revalidated that PHA as documented in correspondence dated March 9, 2018.  The PHA revalidation for the remaining part of the covered process was completed by conducted a fresh PHA in April 2018.  The PHA leader defined the process sections to be assessed and posed relevant operational deviations for the participant to discuss, define concerns, and suggest corrective action items. Each identified action item was assigned to one of the participants to address. This PHA satisfies both of the hazard review requirements for the RMProgram (40 Code of Federal Regulations [CFR] Part 68) and Occupation Safety and Health Administration [OSHA] 29 CFR 1910.119. 



Operating Procedures - Detailed and up-to-date process operating procedures have been developed and are maintained for each covered process in accordance with 40 CFR 68.52. Operating procedures provide clear instructions for safely conducting activities involving a covered process in a manner consistent with process safety information and are readily accessible to employees involved in a covered process. Operating procedures are reviewed annually to ensure that they remain current and accurate.

Operating procedures cover each operating phase of the covered process including:

?    Initial system startup; 

?    Normal operation; 

?    Temporary operations; 

?    Emergency shutdown and operations; 

?    Normal shutdown;

?    Startup following a turnaround or emergency shutdown or major change that requires hazard review, consequences of deviations and steps required to correct or avoid
